President Trump delivered remarks at the U.S. Southern Command headquarters to provide an update on the U.S. military's efforts to combat the flow of illegal drugs across the Western Hemisphere. He praised the progress made in the last few months and highlighted the success of the surge operation conducted by the Southern Command, resulting in over 1,000 arrests and the interdiction of 120 metric tons of narcotics. The President emphasized the importance of securing the country's borders and keeping dangerous drugs away from children. He also discussed the impact of the COVID-19 pandemic on drug overdose deaths and expressed optimism about the economic recovery. Other speakers at the event included Secretary of Defense Mark Esper, Acting Secretary of Homeland Security Chad Wolf, Admiral Craig Faller, and various military and law enforcement officials.